<paragraph id="8BB9368B1974FFB26A8BA703744FFE40" blockId="84.[189,1399,1892,2025]" lastBlockId="85.[189,1399,266,468]" lastPageId="85" lastPageNumber="86" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
HEAD. Face in lateral view concave, strongly projected antero-ventrally; frontal prominence weakly developed. Ratio width of vertex at anterior ocellus: width of head 1: 4.5 ratio width of ocellar triangle: width of vertex 1: 2.0; ratio length of ocellar triangle: length of frons 1: 2.4. Face black, light grey pollinose, long pilose along eye-margin. Hypostomal bridge black, long pale pilose. Gena and mouth edge black with large subtriangular non-pollinose shiny area. Frons and vertex black, slightly pollinose, a wide subtriangular area posterior of lunula non-pollinose and shiny and a wide posterolateral densely grey-pollinose fascia (
<figureCitation id="133D2A0E1975FFB26BF5A137721DFEFE" box="[451,561,336,362]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="86.[189,232,1787,1813]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,412,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@86.[189,1399,412,1739]" captionTargetPageId="86" captionText="Fig. 38. Head, lateral view (C, K), dorsal view (A–B, D, F–J, L) and frontal view (E). A. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) farinosa sp. nov.,holotype, Ƌ, Sabah, Malaysia. B. S. (A.) fimbriata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Thailand. C–D. S. (A.) forceps Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin, 2015, paratype, Ƌ, Myanmar. E. S. (A.) furva Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin, 2015, paratype, Ƌ, Myanmar. F. S. (A.) ghatsi, sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, India. G. S. (A.) gigantea sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, China. H. S. (A.) granditarsis sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Thailand. I. S. (A.) hamulata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, India. J. S. (A.) hansoni Thompson, 1966, holotype, Ƌ, Nepal. K–L. S. (A.) hauseri sp. nov., paratype, Ƌ, Nepal. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830632/files/figure.png" pageId="85" pageNumber="86">Fig. 38G</figureCitation>
); pile short, light yellow. Frons with weak pit antero-medially. Occiput black, light grey pollinose, light yellow pilose. Eye without enlarged facets at anterior margin. Antenna brown with black setae dorsally on scape and pedicel; basoflagellomere squarish, ratio width: length 1: 1.1; arista long pilose, slightly more than 3.5 times as long as basoflagellomere.
</paragraph>
